rComments: I took this class as an elective and enjoyed it! I had played music for quite a long time so the content was not challenging but the course was well taught! For any prior/current musicians I highly recommend this as an elective and for anyone without musical experience, this is a great introduction to the foundations of music theory!

If you have any experience in music/basic theory this class is a very easy A. If not, while she is a bit chaotic, she does start from the very beginning. Also no midterms! I never attended the lectures so I'm not sure about those, but people with no music experience still scored quite well so I assume they did the trick.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: AVOID AT ALL COSTS. So disorganized. Like the worst!!!! Horrible at explaining, treats it like an advanced class. Honestly the worst professor I have ever had.
Extremely talented instructor. She really, really knows her stuff!!

She is not organised. There are 10 assignments (15% of your grade) and you need to keep a copy of then completed because she is not responsible for assignment SHE might lose. If you email her for help, she is going to take days before getting back at you when you will no longer need her help.
